A "smart math solver," often an AI-powered tool, is a digital application or platform that helps users solve math problems by understanding and processing input
from text, images, or handwritten notes.These solvers provide accurate solutions with detailed, step-by-step explanations,helping students, teachers, and professionals improve 
their comprehension of mathematical concepts across various levels, from arithmetic to calculus. They also often offer additional learning resources like practice worksheets 
and video tutorials to support a personalized learning experience. 
